129. esse, ‘exist.’ Lucretius’ argument is that you must not expect to find heterogeneous elements in combination: you do not find clouds in the sea or blood in trees, nor will you find natura consilumque animi (or animus alone) cum quovis corpore.

quovis is emphatic, ‘in any body whatsoever.’
